The paper discusses a new analytical framework for measuring the performance of recommender systems, which is a topic related to information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also mentions the need to pay attention to speed and memory requirements of the algorithms, which is a topic related to machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper proposes to measure the complexity of recommender systems with artificial datasets, which is a topic related to simulation and modeling (cs.SI) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
